    "Therefore, graph pooling methods need to have the ability to handle these structural changes while maintaining stable performance.",
    "However, existing graph pooling methods tend to be overly sensitive to changes in the structure of the graph, resulting in significant performance degradation when the graph structure changes.",
    "In addition, graph data may contain noise and outliers, which may be due to errors in the data collection process, malicious attacks, and so on.",
    "Robust graph pooling methods should have the ability to identify and deal with the effects of these noise and outliers to maintain stable performance.",
    "However, existing graph pooling methods perform poorly when dealing with noise and outliers and are easily affected by them, resulting."
